description: From Middle English undull, equivalent to un- (“not”) +‎ dull.

adjectives.description: undull (comparative more undull, superlative most undull)

verbs.description: undull (third-person singular simple present undulls, present participle undulling, simple past and past participle undulled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove the dullness of; clear.
examples: It is a most musicall Modulator of all Intelligibles by her inventive Variations, undulling their Grossenesse, and subliming it into more refined Acceptablenesse to our own, or others understandings.
